

The way I write my cards is a little unorthodox. I put the entirety of the character's personality and traits into a Lorebook matrix and simply link it to the char(which holds no actual information other than its name and greeting because if this method). It's immensely tedious but surprisingly effective. The format is:

[{{char}} aspect: blah, blah, blah(simple elaboration of blah when needed(possible elaboration of elaboration(nesting each like so))), blah;

Another {{char}} aspect: blah, blah, blah(you get the idea)]

I'm not the best at explaining so this all probably sounded like nonsense but I can elaborate if needed.
